###############################Docker Basics##################################################


1.To run a docker setting
	docker-compose up

2.kill a compose
	docker-compose down --rmi all 	
	
3.Dockerfile:
		FROM node:alpine
		COPY . /app
		WORKDIR /app
		CMD node appjs
		
		
4.build the docker file
			docker build -t hello-docker .
			
5. list images
		docker image ls
		
6.Running a container
			docker run hello-docker
			
			
7.Pull images from docker-hub to other env.
		docker pull dokr-hub/hello-docker
		
8.search play with docker in google and sign in u can check you small images.

9.check running process
		1.docker ps      ---> only running process
		2.docker ps -a   ---> all process
		
		
10.Run  interactive commands in ubuntu
		1.docker run -it ubuntu 
		
		
11.Package Manager
		1.APT - Advanced Packaging Tool
		2.apt install nano
		3.apt list
		4.apt update  (to update apt database)
		5.apt remove nano
		
		
		
		
